    {
      "id": "149fab9280b4d2515cff2ab0451f4a469e3c0da7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 1,
        "name": "Robert Read",
        "email": "robert.read@intel.com",
        "username": "rread",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-08 15:39:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nDoes this happen before the deapply patches step or after?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "c10bd329dee23066f9d6e95e15e0d11ce35706fd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-08 16:05:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt happens in dpkg-buildpackage's de-apply step (i.e. where dpkg-buildpackage is trying to return the tree to it's \"pre-patched\" pristine state).\n\nThe problem arises because we run configure before make debs and that configure creates some files from their .in source.  If one of the files it creates happens to be a file one of the patches (commits) is trying to removed (which means create in deapply context) there is a collision.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
